        <div id="h1">
            Line Railroad Bridge
        </div>

        <div class="information">
            <div class="img">
                <img height="300px" width="450px" src="Soo_Line_RR_Bridge_Eau_Claire.jpg">
            </div>

            <adress style="font-size: x-large; color: black;"> Phoenix Park, Eau Claire, WI 54703 </adress> <BR><BR>
                 Located inside of Phoenix Park in Eau Claire Wisconsin, Line Railroad Bridge 
            <BR> was built in 1910 to replace an older structure. The bridge allowed trains 
            <BR> to pass over the river into a heavily industrial part of the city. Once the
            <BR> railroad wasn't used as often the tracks were taken down. 
            <BR>
            <BR> Roughly 10 years later in 2002 the bridge was opened up to pedestrians. 
            <BR> The bridge is 442 feet long and has slight curves that were used to allow 
            <BR> the train to weave back and forth without being to sharp for a train to 
            <BR> pass over. The bridge is in the National Register of Historic Places after
            <BR> it's rich history in the city of Eau Claire. It is now a place that is hiked 
            <BR> over and heavily visited for it's importance to the city. 
            <BR>
            <BR> More History - <a href="https://www.leadertelegram.com/news/front-page/eau-claires-s-bridge-joins-national-register-of-historic-places/article_c79c1932-f455-5e57-869f-271580533230.html" target="_blank" color="blue">leadertelegram.com</a>
